    "body": "<span class=\"solution-visible-txt\">All submissions for this problem are available.</span><p>\nChef and Mahi are good friends. Chef Likes to play with Numbers he is very good at maths. Chef has <b>N</b> distinct Numbers with him in sorted order. Chef always make fun of Mahi as he is a medical student, He doesn't know maths.<br/> <br/>Chef thinks of a game called \"Game of Numbers\". Here are rules of the Game. <br/><br />\nTake an integer <b>A</b> \u2264 N. And Let,<br/><br />\nS<sub>A</sub> be the number of ways in which first 'A' numbers from the set of Numbers can be arranged in any order. <br/><br />\nS<sub>A+1</sub> be the number of ways in which first 'A+1' numbers from the set of Numbers can be arranged in any order.<br />\n.<br/><br />\n.<br/><br />\n.<br/><br />\nS<sub>N</sub> be the number of ways in which first 'N' number from the set can be arranged in any order. <br/></br/></br/></br/></br/></br/></br/></br/></br/></br/></p>\n<p>Then find the sum of above Computations that is S<sub>A</sub> + S<sub>A+1</sub> + S<sub>A+2</sub> + ..... + S<sub>N</sub>.<br />\n<br/><br />\nNow chef explained the Game to Mahi and they Both started playing. Mahi needs your help in this game.<br />\n<br/><br/><br />\n<b>NOTE:</b> Output Can be Very Large print it as <b>ans</b> mod <b>10<sup>9</sup>+7</b>. </br/></br/></br/></p>\n<h3>Input</h3>\n<li>The first line of input contains an integer T denoting the number of test cases.</li>\n<li>Each test case consists of single line and it contains values <b>A</b> and <b>N</b> respectively.</li>\n<h3>Output</h3>\n<p>For each test case, print a single line giving the answer to the problem.</p>\n<h3>Constraints</h3>\n<li>1 \u2264 T \u2264 50000</li>\n<li>1 \u2264 A \u2264 N \u2264 10<sup>6</sup></li>\n<h3>Example</h3>\n<pre><b>Input:</b>\n2\n2 5\n3 6\n<b>Output:</b>\n152\n870\n</pre><p>\u00a0</p>\n<h3>Explanation</h3>\n<p><b>Example case 1.</b>ans = S<sub>2</sub>+S<sub>3</sub>+S<sub>4</sub>+S<sub>5</sub> and then ans <b>mod</b> 10<sup>9</sup>+7</p>\n",
